_About ME/CFS:_

_ME/CFS is a chronic neuroimmune illness—not depression, laziness, or "just being tired." Key features:_

_1. Post-exertional malaise: Activity causes symptom worsening 12–72 hours later. A student who seems fine during class may crash the next day._

_2. Cognitive dysfunction ("brain fog"): Difficulty concentrating, processing information, and remembering—even when appearing alert._

_3. Energy limits: Students have a fixed "energy envelope." Exceeding it causes crashes and potentially long-term worsening._

_What helps: Flexible deadlines, reduced workload, rest breaks, quiet environment, believing the student's reported symptoms._

_What hurts: Pressure to "push through," skepticism about symptoms, inconsistent accommodation implementation, comparing student to peers._

